<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="441" pageId="9" pageNumber="440" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1960,2023]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1437,151,861]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="441" pageId="9" pageNumber="440">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1960,1986]" pageId="9" pageNumber="440">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Kamiya" authorityName="Kamiya" authorityYear="1963" box="[557,787,1960,1986]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Axinoscymnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="440" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beneficus">
<emphasis box="[557,692,1960,1986]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="440">A. beneficus</emphasis>
Kamiya
</taxonomicName>
in the elytral colour patterns but can be distinguished from the latter by the stout penis with blunt apex according to the illustrations given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pang, X. F. &amp; Gordon, R. D." box="[1089,1354,1996,2023]" pageId="9" pageNumber="440" pagination="157 - 199" refId="ref16560" refString="Pang, X. F. &amp; Gordon, R. D. (1986) The Scymnini (Coleoptera: Coccinellidae) of China. The Coleopterists Bulletin, 40 (2), 157 - 199." type="journal article" year="1986">Pang &amp; Gordon (1986)</bibRefCitation>
. It also resembles with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Sicard)" baseAuthorityName="Sicard" box="[327,544,151,178]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Axinoscymnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="441" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fumatus">
<emphasis box="[327,447,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">A. fumatus</emphasis>
(Sicard)
</taxonomicName>
in the dark brown elytra and stout penis, but can be separated from the latter by its elytra with yellowish brown basal margin (
<figureCitation box="[665,747,187,214]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1584,1608]" captionTargetBox="[170,1418,901,1548]" captionTargetId="figure-274@10.[151,1436,885,1561]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Axinoscymnus singaporicus Pang et Gordon, 1986 (Paratype): a dorsal view b ventral view c lateral view d labels of paratype. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5mm." pageId="10" pageNumber="441">Fig. 6a</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="441" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,222,248]" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">Description.</emphasis>
TL: 
<quantity box="[402,568,222,249]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.68" metricValueMax="1.71" metricValueMin="1.65" pageId="10" pageNumber="441" unit="mm" value="1.68" valueMax="1.71" valueMin="1.65">1.65–1.71 mm</quantity>
, TW: 
<quantity box="[638,804,223,249]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.205" metricValueMax="1.22" metricValueMin="1.19" pageId="10" pageNumber="441" unit="mm" value="1.205" valueMax="1.22" valueMin="1.19">1.19–1.22 mm</quantity>
, TH: 
<quantity box="[869,1034,223,249]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="9.2" metricValueMin="8.8" pageId="10" pageNumber="441" unit="mm" value="0.9" valueMax="0.92" valueMin="0.88">0.88–0.92 mm</quantity>
, TL/TW: 1.35–1.44, EL/EW: 1.04– 1.11, PL/PW: 0.48–0.52, HW/PW: 0.67–0.69, PW/EW: 0.67–0.70.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">
Body oval, moderately convex, dorsum with pale yellow pubescence (
<figureCitation box="[992,1107,295,322]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1584,1608]" captionTargetBox="[170,1418,901,1548]" captionTargetId="figure-274@10.[151,1436,885,1561]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Axinoscymnus singaporicus Pang et Gordon, 1986 (Paratype): a dorsal view b ventral view c lateral view d labels of paratype. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5mm." pageId="10" pageNumber="441">Figs 6a–c</figureCitation>
). Head, antennae and mouthparts yellow (
<figureCitation box="[303,386,331,358]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1584,1608]" captionTargetBox="[170,1418,901,1548]" captionTargetId="figure-274@10.[151,1436,885,1561]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Axinoscymnus singaporicus Pang et Gordon, 1986 (Paratype): a dorsal view b ventral view c lateral view d labels of paratype. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5mm." pageId="10" pageNumber="441">Fig. 6b</figureCitation>
), tip of mandibles dark brown. Pronotum and scutellar shield yellow. Elytra dark brown, basal margin yellowish brown (
<figureCitation box="[443,559,367,394]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1584,1608]" captionTargetBox="[170,1418,901,1548]" captionTargetId="figure-274@10.[151,1436,885,1561]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Axinoscymnus singaporicus Pang et Gordon, 1986 (Paratype): a dorsal view b ventral view c lateral view d labels of paratype. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5mm." pageId="10" pageNumber="441">Figs 6a–c</figureCitation>
). Prothoracic hypomeron and prosternum yellow. Mesoventrite and metaventrite dark brown. Elytral epipleurae black. Legs yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">
Head with fine frontal punctures, as large as eye facets, 1.0–1.5 diameters apart. Eyes densely faceted, interocular distance about 0.27 times of head width (
<figureCitation box="[596,677,475,502]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1584,1608]" captionTargetBox="[170,1418,901,1548]" captionTargetId="figure-274@10.[151,1436,885,1561]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Axinoscymnus singaporicus Pang et Gordon, 1986 (Paratype): a dorsal view b ventral view c lateral view d labels of paratype. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5mm." pageId="10" pageNumber="441">Fig. 6b</figureCitation>
). Pronotal punctures slightly larger than those on frons, 1.0–1.5 diameters apart. Surface of elytra with punctures much larger than those on pronotum, separated by 1.0–2.0 diameters.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">
Male genitalia. The male genitalia of the 
<typeStatus box="[657,753,547,573]" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">paratype</typeStatus>
we examined were lost. For detailed illustrations see 
<bibRefCitation author="Pang, X. F. &amp; Gordon, R. D." pageId="10" pageNumber="441" pagination="157 - 199" refId="ref16560" refString="Pang, X. F. &amp; Gordon, R. D. (1986) The Scymnini (Coleoptera: Coccinellidae) of China. The Coleopterists Bulletin, 40 (2), 157 - 199." type="journal article" year="1986">Pang &amp; Gordon (1986)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
