<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="441" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,304,727,753]" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">Remark.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[367,465,727,753]" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">holotype</typeStatus>
of this species is deposited in the collection of the 
<collectingCountry box="[1069,1222,727,753]" name="United States of America" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">United States</collectingCountry>
National Museum (USNM), 
<collectingRegion box="[267,404,763,789]" country="United States of America" name="Washington" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">Washington</collectingRegion>
. Two 
<typeStatus box="[475,571,763,789]" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">paratype</typeStatus>
specimens were preserved in the collection of Department of Entomology, South 
<collectingCountry box="[223,290,799,825]" name="China" pageId="10" pageNumber="441">China</collectingCountry>
Agricultural University (SCAU). However, these 
<specimenCount box="[848,1004,799,825]" pageId="10" pageNumber="441" type="generic" typeStatus="paratypes">two paratypes</specimenCount>
are discolored and their male genitalia were lost.
</paragraph>
